nodes.bodyText: These files are new and should not be deleted (they came in since you merged with master).
These files are new and should not be deleted (they came in since you merged with master).
Since junit is already used for the test results (junit plugin) we need to use a different name here: what about junitParser.
Overwrite getUrl with link to JUnit.
Can you check if we can include the JUnit 5 logo as well? It would be niche to have the reports linked with the official new logo https://junit.org/junit5/.

How will I link the reports with junit logo?
Should I download and store the logo into icons folder and use override getLabelProvider() in JUnit.java
Yes, you need to overwrite that method, here is an example: https://github.com/jenkinsci/warnings-ng-plugin/blob/master/src/main/java/io/jenkins/plugins/analysis/warnings/EsLint.java#L69
The icons belong to the icons folder and should be in 48x48 and 24x24 PNG. In the near feature I will change that to SVG but we can add that later on...

Ok. thanks, Do you know if they did specify the license somewhere? Then we can add a corresponding line in https://github.com/jenkinsci/warnings-ng-plugin/blob/master/src/main/webapp/icons/LICENSE.txt

They have a license for the source code distribution https://github.com/junit-team/junit5/blob/master/LICENSE.md.
THE ACCOMPANYING PROGRAM IS PROVIDED UNDER THE TERMS OF THIS ECLIPSE PUBLIC LICENSE (“AGREEMENT”). ANY USE, REPRODUCTION OR DISTRIBUTION OF THE PROGRAM CONSTITUTES RECIPIENT'S ACCEPTANCE OF THIS AGREEMENT.
Should I ask them ?
That would be nice! I always have a bad feeling with icons that do not have the license correctly set.

Yes, wonderful! You can link to the GitHub issue in the license.txt file.
Please also add the URL to JUnit with getUrl (see comment above) and then I will merge your changes!
Sorry for not mentioning it beforehand, but I have already added the URL to JUnit with getUrl().
